  {
    "id": "10.1016/j.ast.2026.112068",
    "title": "Contrail aging of a supersonic aircraft using a RANS/LES approach",
    "authors": "Mathieu Muller, Etienne Terrenoire, Younes Bouhafid, Nicolas Bonne",
    "abstract": "The redevelopment of supersonic aircrafts is currently taking place for aircraft such as business jet also call bizjet. Main advantages are related to the drastic reduction of the effective time travel for a given mission but their climate impact remains uncertain. The objective of this work is to model and characterize the condensation trails (contrails) generated by the E-19 Aeolus’s supersonic “concept plane” using the Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD) CEDRE code.. First, the global approach using CEDRE and a mesh adaptation procedure are presented.. Secondly, the Reynolds Averaged Navier-Stokes (RANS) simulation of the contrail formation (jet phase, t ∼ 1s) are described and analysed, with a focus on both aerodynamics and microphysics aspects. Third, the contrail aging up to 2 min is modelled using a Large Eddy Simulation (LES) approach, and the contrail intrinsic characteristics obtained for the E-19 aircraft are analysed and finally some conclusions and perspectives are proposed in the last section of the paper.",
